I think the reason the vacuumed steak didn't cook so well was likely due to heat sink from all the extra material absorbing the heat from the element, as well as the heat being drawn away through the vacuum itself.

It would be interesting to try it again in such a way that it is cooked properly, and the comparing that properly cooked steak to a normally cooked, properly done steak.
